  <!-- Section: Common Mistakes -->
  <section id="mistakes" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Overstaying Your Visa</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Overstay fines are $100/day, plus potential deportation and entry bans. Set extension reminders 2+ weeks ahead. Never cut it close.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Riding Motorbikes Without License</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Many insurance policies void coverage without a valid motorcycle license. Get an International Driving Permit before arrival, or a local license in Bali.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Skipping Insurance</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Hospital bills, dengue treatment, or Singapore medevac can be catastrophic without insurance. The $50-100/month is essential, not optional.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Using Cheap Unknown Agents</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Scam visa agents exist. Use agents recommended in established nomad communities. Pay a bit more for reliability.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Expecting Western Infrastructure</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Power outages, slow internet days, and traffic are real. Have backup plans for important calls. Starlink is becoming popular.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Tax Residency Issues</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Staying 183+ days may trigger Indonesian tax residency. Track your days carefully or plan exit trips to stay under the threshold.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

